Class MentorshipRecord<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • lib.MentorshipRecord<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - 

    public class MentorshipRecord<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    The MentorshipRecord class creates and define methods to be implemented within the MentorshipRecord Demo class. Not all methods within this class will be demonstrated.
    Author:
    P2536632 The class is of generic type E.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MentorshipRecord

        public MentorshipRecord(E data)
        Constructor used to create a new node object.
        Parameters:
        data - is used to specify a student's P-number. It must start with a 'P' and contain seven numbers. Enter as a String. Only root does not have a P-number.

      • MentorshipRecord

        public MentorshipRecord(E data,
                        MentorshipRecord<E> parent)
        Constructor used to create a new node object, and define a hierarchical link between itself and it's parent node.
        Parameters:
        data - is used to specify a student's P-number. It must start with a 'P' and contain seven numbers. Enter as a String.
        parent - is used to specify which node the new node is directly descendant from. It must be the name of a node that already exists.

      • removeMentor

        public static void removeMentor(MentorshipRecord<java.lang.String> startSearchAt,
                                java.lang.String mentorsString)
        Removes a specified mentor node, using the mentorsString param. It's descendants are also removed if it is both a mentee and a mentor. If the specified node is not a mentor, the operation will not function. Pushes all relevant nodes to be deleted to a list (ToBeRemoved), which is passed onto the removeSelected() method.
        Parameters:
        startSearchAt - States where the search should begin. Recommended to be a parent node.
        mentorsString - The P-number of the mentor to be deleted.

      • removeMentee

        public static void removeMentee(MentorshipRecord<java.lang.String> startSearchAt,
                                java.lang.String menteesString)
        Removes a specified mentee node, using the menteesString param. It's descendants are also removed if it is both a mentee and a mentor. If the specified node is not a menteee, the operation will not function. Pushes all relevant nodes to be deleted to a list (ToBeRemoved), which is passed onto the removeSelected() method.
        Parameters:
        startSearchAt - States where the search should begin. Recommended to be a parent node.
        menteesString - The P-number of the mentee to be deleted.

                                java.lang.String mentorsString,
                                MentorshipRecord<java.lang.String> newMenteeToAssign)
        Assigns a given mentor to a given mentee using the params. The operation will not function if a mentor or mentee is null or if the mentor is not a mentor. Use this method to add a newly created node to the tree.
        Parameters:
        startSearchAt - States where the search should begin. Recommended to be a parent node.

        newMenteeToAssign - The newly created mentee to be assigned to the mentor.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when the entered nodes are null.

      • searchForMentor

        public static <E> java.util.Optional<?> searchForMentor(MentorshipRecord<java.lang.String> startSearchAt,
                                                        java.lang.String searchFor)
        Searches the tree for data from one given node using the startSearchAt param until it finds the String value passed using the searchFor param. Returns true if there is a match and outputs all nodes within the traversed paths. Returns false if there is no match and outputs all nodes within the traversed paths. If the node specified is not a mentor, the operation will return false.
        Type Parameters:
        E -
        Parameters:
        startSearchAt - The node which the search will begin from. Recommended to be a parent node.
        searchFor - The P-number string to find a match with. Must belong to a mentor.
        Returns:
        True or false depending on the match with all nodes from the traversed paths.

      • findMenteesOfMentor

                                                        java.lang.String searchFor)
        Finds and outputs all mentee children of a given mentor. If the mentor param is not a mentor or is root, the operation will not function.
        Parameters:
        startSearchAt - The node which the search will begin from. Recommended to be a parent node.
        searchFor - The P-number string to find a match with. Must belong to a mentor.
        Returns:
        All of the mentees belonging to a mentor.
